<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01064d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01064d">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01064d"> 64(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> no of 1<sup>st</sup> P C to arrest hood or / cribcrack. new moon bad / never rob knife or / 1 armed man</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[THIEVES&apos; SUPERSTITIONS. By CHRISTOPHER BECK.]</font> Certain times and seasons are unpopular with Bill Sykes <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Numbers count for much with the <mark>crib-cracking</mark> fraternity. Each man has his lucky or unlucky numbers. A man who has been arrested or convicted never forgets the <mark>number of the policeman who arrested him</mark>, and considers this number to be his &ldquo;<mark>hoodoo</mark>.&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Not only must you <mark>never steal a knife</mark>, but also you must <mark>never rob a one-armed man</mark>. To do so means all kinds of ill-luck. <small> <a name="DM11dec22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DM11dec22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (11 December 1922) 8/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05132e" href="c05all.htm#c05132e">VI.C.05:132(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
